quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  3,1,Alif Lam Mim
  3,2,"Allah, there is no god but Him, the Living, the Self-Sustaining"
  3,3,"He has sent down the Book to you with truth, confirming what was there before it. And He sent down the Torah and the Gospel"
  3,4,"previously, as guidance for mankind, and He has sent down the Furqan"
  3,5,"Those who reject Allah´s Signs will have a terrible punishment. Allah is Almighty, Exactor of Revenge"
  3,6,"Allah — Him from Whom nothing is hidden, either on earth or in heaven. It is He who forms you in the womb however He wills. There is no god but Him, the Almighty, the All-Wise"
  3,7,"It is He who sent down the Book to you from Him: ayats containing clear judgements — they are the core of the Book — and others which are open to interpretation. Those with deviation in their hearts follow what is open to interpretation in it, desiring conflict, seeking its inner meaning. No one knows its inner meaning but Allah. Those firmly rooted in knowledge say, ´We have iman in it. All of it is from our Lord.´ But only people of intelligence pay heed"
  3,8,"´Our Lord, do not make our hearts swerve aside after You have guided us. And give us mercy from You. You are the Ever-Giving"
  3,9,"Our Lord, You are the Gatherer of mankind to a Day of which there is no doubt. Allah will not break His promise.´"